triggers               package:phyRtools               R Documentation

_M_a_r_k _s_p_i_k_e_s _b_y _t_h_e_i_r _n_e_a_r_e_s_t _t_r_i_g_g_e_r

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     A function which creates a new ‘phyoutput’ object only containing
     spikes near a trigger (as specified by ‘back’ & ‘forward’).

_U_s_a_g_e:

     triggers(x, back = 500, forward = 600)
     
_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

       x: A list object as created by ‘loadSpikes’

    back: The time in ms to look backwards from trigger. Defaults to
          500.

 forward: The time in ms to look forwards from trigger. Defaults to
          600.

_V_a_l_u_e:

     A new phyouput object containing info and spikes near triggers.

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

     dt <- loadSpikes(path, triggerfile)
     newdt <- triggers(dt)
     

